  ## Verify OTP
  
  ### Endpoint
  `POST /verify-otp`
  
  ### Description
  Verifies a one-time password (OTP) sent to the userâ€™s email (typically for registration or password reset).
  
  ### Request
  - **Method:** POST
  - **Auth:** None
  - **Body (multipart-form):**
    - `email`: string (required)
    - `code`: string (required)
  
  ### Success Response
  ```json
  {
    "status": "success",
    "message": "OTP verified successfully.",
    "data": {
      "email": "user@example.com",
      "first_name": "John",
      "verified": true,
      "access": "access_token",
      "refresh": "refresh_token",
      "first_login": false
    }
  }
  ```
  
  ### Error Response
  ```json
  {
    "status": "error",
    "message": "Invalid data",
    "errors": {
      "code": "Invalid or expired code"
    }
  }
  ```
